transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, Quinn speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I want to cancel this order.

Speaker 1: The prescription that...

Speaker 2: Is your name Robert Leonard?

Speaker 1: Yes, it is.

Speaker 2: Okay. What's going on with the Viagra? Why don't you want it anymore, sir?

Speaker 1: It doesn't work.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay. Well, this is definitely a body chemistry type of medication.

Speaker 1: If it's not working, we can send you something different.

Speaker 2: That's usually the case of finding something to work for free—

Speaker 1: —and stop sending you this current one that's not working.

Speaker 2: No, I just want to stop it.

Speaker 1: I'm tired of trying stuff.

Speaker 2: Okay. All right. We'll cancel it.

Speaker 1: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Have a good day.
